Conversely, lower water temperatures slow down this extraction process, requiring a longer steeping time to reach the same strength. For example, black teas typically require near-boiling water (around 100°C or 212°F) and a steeping time of 3-5 minutes, while green teas are best brewed at lower temperatures (around 70-80°C or 158-176°F) for 2-3 minutes.
